  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what the bug is and steps to reproduce it.-->\r\n\r\nIf a validator calls `produceAggregateAndProof` with an `attestationData` that does not match any attestation a TypeError will happen while trying to reduce an empty array with no initial value.\r\n\r\n```\r\n2020-07-18 20:29:33  [VALIDATOR #0-13] error: Failed to produce aggregate and proof Error: Reduce of empty array with no initial value\r\nTypeError: Reduce of empty array with no initial value\r\n    at Array.reduce (<anonymous>)\r\n    at ValidatorApi.produceAggregateAndProof (/home/lion/Code/eth2.0/lodestar/packages/lodestar/src/api/impl/validator/validator.ts:110:12)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:94:5)\r\n    at Timeout._onTimeout (/home/lion/Code/eth2.0/lodestar/packages/lodestar-validator/src/services/attestation.ts:188:27)\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/1068d6e828699df04cd606ad5498ef7a85720ce8/packages/lodestar/src/api/impl/validator/validator.ts#L183\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.-->\r\n\r\nThis occurrence should be handled better.\r\n\r\n1. A more clear error should be thrown, i.e. `No matching attestations found for attestationData`\r\n2. Return the original attestation data without any extra aggregated signature.\r\n\r\nThis error can potentially prevent the validator from submitting the attestation? If so we should go with 2.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n<!--Steps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to '...'\r\n2. Click on '....'\r\n3. Scroll down to '....'\r\n4. See error\r\n-->\r\n\r\nIt's a common occurrence when running this test in a 1 node, 8 validators configuration\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/6d13626135948786682379c36a65f9f0ea9c70e4/packages/lodestar/test/e2e/noEth1Sim.test.ts\r\n\r\n",
